OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,F"An engaging gaze meets the viewer
OL,7,Ffrom the centre of the banknote. It
OL,8,Fencapsulates a proposal, an idea and a
OL,9,Fdialogue between those who have forged
OL,10,Four cultural identity and those of us
OL,11,Fwho are making Europe a place at the
OL,12,Fforefront of thought, keeping the
OL,13,Fspirit of these figures alive in our
OL,14,Fdaily lives. A dominant, consistent
OL,15,Fand recognisable colour meets a linear
OL,16,Fpattern that provides a shared
OL,17,Ftexture, within a structure that holds
OL,18,Fthe whole together. If we turn the
OL,19,Fbanknotes horizontally, we see four
OL,20,Fvertical blocks, each inspired by a
OL,21,Fletter: 'E', 'U', 'R' and 'O'."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
