CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,F"The design tells a simple story:
OL,7,FEurope is a shared cultural space.
OL,8,FEach banknote is instantly
OL,9,Fidentifiable by its dominant colour
OL,10,Fand its own central motif; each
OL,11,Fportrays a personality whose life and
OL,12,Fwork connects Europeans across
OL,13,Fcenturies. The reverse pairs a map of
OL,14,FEurope, lightly overlaid with the
OL,15,Fconstellations that have long guided
OL,16,Ftravellers, with a present-day scene
OL,17,Fof the cultural space the note
OL,18,Frepresents ` performing arts, music,
OL,19,Fschools, libraries, museums and public
OL,20,Fsquares. People are rendered without
OL,21,Fspecific features so that citizens can
OL,22,Frecognise themselves in them."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
