PN,30422
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,F"The 'Rivers and birds' banknote
OL,7,Fseries communicates its concept
OL,8,Fthrough a direct connection between
OL,9,Fvisual elements and their meaning.
OL,10,FEach banknote presents a specific bird
OL,11,Fspecies in relation to its habitat,
OL,12,Flinking biodiversity with European
OL,13,Flandscapes. Horizontal bar structures
OL,14,Ftranslate the individual sound of each
OL,15,Fbird into a visual form, while a
OL,16,Fvertical scale indicates its flight
OL,17,Fspeed, enabling an intuitive reading
OL,18,Fof the information. Concise data on
OL,19,Fthe front further contextualise the
OL,20,Fspecies. On the reverse, EU buildings
OL,21,Fand the map of Europe establish a
OL,22,Fconnection between natural
OL,23,Fenvironments and shared cultural
OL,24,Fidentity."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
