OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,F"The design can be explained as a
OL,7,Freflection on how culture is formed.
OL,8,FThe eyes represent observing, sensing
OL,9,Fand reflecting, while the mouth
OL,10,Fsymbolises expression, dialogue and
OL,11,Fexchange. By focusing on these
OL,12,Felements, the portraits move beyond
OL,13,Findividual identity towards a shared
OL,14,Fhuman capacity for cultural
OL,15,Fproduction. On the reverse,
OL,16,Fcontemporary cultural spaces show
OL,17,Fpeople of different backgrounds and
OL,18,Fages meeting and interacting.
OL,19,FTogether, the two sides connect
OL,20,Findividual perception and expression
OL,21,Fwith collective exchange, inviting the
OL,22,Fpublic to see the banknotes as
OL,23,Frepresentations of culture as a
OL,24,Fliving, shared process."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G24/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30425
SC,0025
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,FWhat's behind the new design proposals?
OL,8,FChristine Lagarde, President of the
OL,9,FECB said: "After 20 years, it's time
OL,10,Fto review the look of our banknotes to
OL,11,Fmake them more relatable to Europeans
OL,12,Fof all ages and backgrounds."
OL,14,FThe theme of the last set of banknotes
OL,15,Fwas "ages and styles" depicting
OL,16,Ffictional bridges and architectural
OL,17,Fmonuments.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G25/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30426
SC,0026
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,FTwo options were selected for the
OL,7,Fredesign proposals, with the first
OL,8,Fbeing "European Culture: Shared
OL,9,FCultural Spaces", and the second
OL,10,F"Rivers and Birds: Resilience in
OL,11,Fdiversity".
OL,13,FThe ECB council then selected the
OL,14,Fmotifs that would appear on each note
OL,15,Fin keeping with these themes;
OL,16,Fdesigners were then invited to submit
OL,17,Ftheir ideas for how each image should
OL,18,Fbe depicted.
OL,20,FWhy the change?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G26/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30427
SC,0027
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784913523
OL,3,CWhy euro notes are being redesigned -
OL,4,Cand how you can have a say
OL,6,FThe European Central Bank (ECB) says
OL,7,Fthe redesign is necessary to "better
OL,8,Freflect Europe's shared identity and
OL,9,Fvalues".
OL,11,FIn an explanation on its website, it
OL,12,Fwrites: "Euro banknotes are a tangible
OL,13,Freflection of Europe's shared
OL,14,Fidentity, diversity and values.
OL,16,F"More relatable motifs can further
OL,17,Fstrengthen the bond between Europeans
OL,18,Fand their currency."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G27/33
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
